          "locator": "0",
          "object_type": null,
          "text": "Definition 5 A square matrix A = [ a ij ] is said to be skew symmetric matrix if A ‚Ä≤ = ‚Äď A, that is a ji = ‚Äď a ij for all possible values of i and j . Now, if we put i = j , we have a ii = ‚Äď a ii . Therefore 2 a ii = 0 or a ii = 0 for all i ‚Äôs.",
          "latex": []
        },
        {
          "concept_id": "concept.0e3243205095",
          "concept_name": "skew symmetric matrix",
          "source_field": "definition_texts",
          "locator": "1",
          "object_type": null,
          "text": "This means that all the diagonal elements of a skew symmetric matrix are zero.",
          "latex": []
        },
        {
